<div>
  <p>
    The source code lives on
    <a href="https://github.com/arangodb/arangodb" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    There are branches for the different major/minor releases together
    with tags for the individual releases (e.g. <code>3.4</code> branch
    and <code>v3.4.1</code> tag). In general you will not
    need the source packages, unless you want to
    <a href="https://docs.arangodb.com/3.4/Cookbook/Compiling/" target="_blank">compile</a>
    ArangoDB on an operating system not supported by us.
  </p>
  <hr/>
  <p>Source Packages for <strong>C++11 Compilers</strong>
